  "text": "Previous studies have identified several classic risk factors for the development of AMD, and many of these risk factors are also linked to the risk of developing nAMD in the fellow eye (Table 2) , including the presence of AMD in the first eye, the large presence of drusen, or retinal pigmentary abnormalities. 17 In addition, the characteristics of lesions in the fellow eye are frequently similar to the characteristics of lesions in the first eye, including large fibrosis, hemorrhagic tendency, and the presence of retinal angiomatous proliferation. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ",
